<subSubSection id="6D837C851005FF9ADBE2F9AA4D682C6E" pageId="32" pageNumber="133" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E1005FF9ADBE2F9AA4D682C6E" blockId="32.[151,1437,1473,1859]" pageId="32" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1005FF9ADBE2F9AA4D0E2DD6" bold="true" box="[199,315,1761,1787]" pageId="32" pageNumber="133">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1005FF9ADA66F9AA4DC92DD6" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,508,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulawesiensis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1005FF9ADA66F9AA4DC92DD6" box="[323,508,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="133">A. sulawesiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1005FF9AD9EBF9AA4F702DD6" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[718,837,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1005FF9AD9EBF9AA4F702DD6" box="[718,837,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="133">A. magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the head with weak sculpture between the compound eyes, and a narrowly fused mesopresternum and mesoeusternum. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1005FF9ADE02F84E49A92C32" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[1319,1436,1797,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1005FF9ADE02F84E49A92C32" box="[1319,1436,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="133">A. magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the key above.
</paragraph>
